	   <a name=99436986983692></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99436986983692><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=99436986983692>RE: Hand to Hand Skill</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=99436986983692#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17094><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>397 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jul 5th 5:51 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.84]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Praetor is right, as usual. In an effort to ensure that hand to hand skills don't infringe on Monk abilities, Verant has made it clear that non-Monk hand to hand skills are, and will always be, limited. There is little if anything to be gained.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>48th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
