	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jul 3rd 1:24 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.84]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Unless you have a desire to take up a trade skill, you should look into your weapon skills. Unless you have been very good about switching weapons and ensuring all your melee skills are kept up, (not an easy task by any means) you will have some melee skills that can probably be improved.<br><br>Check into your 1-hand blunt skill, or maybe your 2-hand blunt skill. The blunt skills are often overlooked by many paladins.&nbsp;&nbsp;What about your piercing skill?  Have you kept your Archery skill up? If you've been fighting two-handed you may need to improve your Bash skill, and if you've ONLY been fighting 1-handed with shield, maybe you need to improve your 2-hand slash skill? <br><br>If you have truly kept all of those up and have nothing to spend your points on, then I salute you! You are the exception and not the rule.<br><br>Hope this helps,<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>48th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
