	   <tr><td colspan=2>One Other Quick point I would like to make is that we Paladins do have a spell that soothes a mob & When it actually works, we can pull the mob standing next to it. <br>I only use this spell in group scenario or when i am soloing near a zone, It semmed that it only worked 50 % off the time or less.<br>However, with my Deep Water arms (21ac) the effect is a triggered soothe or calm (can't remember) but it works with a very high degree of success, i am finding, so long as i use archery to pull the mob next to the one i soothed(or calmed). I have not failed yet in 5 attempts.<br>I thot i would just throw that out there as a counter for Monks to be pulling when its important to just pull single mobs.<br>We are SOOO versatile, with the right equipment!<br>Torsk Holynite, Ad Gloriam<br>Dwarf paladin of the 45th Season<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
