	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Shaiserosia!<br><br>I too play on the Torvonnilous server. Give me a shout sometime!<br><br>As for Stamina/Hp items, here are just a few suggestions. You may already have some of them.<br><br>Greaves of Ro: AC 13, +6 Sta, +10 Sv Cold<br>Bracer of Scavenging: AC 9, +5 Dex, +5 Sta<br>Ry'Gorr Chain Collar: AC 9, +4 Sta, +4 Sv Magic, +10 mana<br>Ry'Gorr Chain Legs: AC 13, +2 Dex, +2 Sta, +5 hps, +5 sv Cold, +3 Sv Magic<br>Dusty Breastplate: AC 22, +5 Sta, +20 hit pts (both Stamina & Hps)<br><br>I would also encourage you to look into the Ice Forged Shackle Quest in Velious, starting in Ice Clad.&nbsp;&nbsp;You get a very nice bracer that is: AC 10, +5 Str, +5 Dex, +5 Agi, and +30 hit pts.<br><br>You can also improve your hit pts with some of the various rings available.  If you can't afford the +6 AC, +65 hit pt Velium Fire Wedding Bands, then the +5 AC, +55 hit pt Platinum Fire Wedding Bands are a great choice for a High Elf.  You get GREAT hit point bonuses.  I would check into those.  The Velium ones are kinda pricey, but the platinum ones have come down in price significantly of late.<br><br>Look me up! Seems like I'm always on. I'll help if I can.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>48th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
