	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmm, as a paldin, we solo very well. But, in your 30s & later the benefits of a guild, or a group of diverse good freinds that will go out of their way to help you in a pinch, becomes more essential. To complete some of your mid-range quest items, like soulfire, u need the support of a group , or guild. I use the term guild from now on to describe that relationship. When a guild freind needs help to recover a corpse, or to complete a part or their epic quest, will you be there for them, if you are, they will be there for you, when u need em. The Guild that I joined believe in haveing Fun together, the guild is diverse in classes as well as levels, We do guild events & we do not believe in twinking, The rule is to never give a guild item to a player that cannot reasonably attain that item, a few exceptions for alts. The guild raid moto is need before greed, & to encouraGE members to advance in levels, certain raids for class armour or stuff are set up when the players reach milestone levels. <br>My personal opinion on the guild matter , is that i searched a long time to find a guild that opperates with perameters that i like to work in, & have fun with. There are moments when the guild brothers needs my help or involvement & I am there for them. I cannot attain my epic stuff without help, neither can they. The best guilds also have initiation periods, to check you, and your style of play out, before they accept you into thier guild, this is fair enough. <br>I did not join a guild until i was level 32 , I should have joined one earlier, in hindsight. <br>I am appreciating, more & more the trouble that we can get ourselves into. I'ts nice to know there is someone that we can call , that will help us out, & have fun in the process, Hehe<br>Torsk Holynite Ad Gloriam<br>Dwarf Paladin of the 41st Season<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
